We want you to know

While Alexa Voice Remote Pro is compatible with most Fire TV streaming media players, Amazon Fire TV smart TVs, and other popular TVs, soundbars, and A/V receivers, it is not compatible with all brands or models. Compatibility with most smart TVs with Fire TV built-in will be available in the coming months. We recommend using this compatibility guide to ensure Alexa Voice Remote Pro is compatible with your device before placing an order.

The Remote Finder feature has a range of up to 30ft (10m) and requires the Fire TV device to be on. Learn more here.

Remote includes 4 pre-programed app buttons including Prime Video and Netflix; other 2 app buttons will vary.

Remote only
  • “Alexa, find my remote.” - Use a device with Alexa, the Alexa app or Fire TV app and Alexa Voice Remote Pro will emit a ring. No searching cushions.
  • Backlit for your convenience - Navigate movie night with a motion-activated backlight that illuminates buttons in dimly-lit rooms.
  • Two customizable buttons - Create your own shortcuts to favorite channels, apps, or any Alexa commands.
  • Dedicated headphone button - A new shortcut to the on-screen Bluetooth menu that lets you pair your wireless headphones fast.
  • Integrated TV controls - Control power, volume, plus surf live TV with dedicated channel buttons all from one remote.
  • Press and ask Alexa - Use your voice to find your shows, open apps, manage volume, and even control compatible smart home devices.
  • Compatible with most Fire TV streaming media players, Amazon Fire TV smart TVs, and smart TVs with Fire TV built-in.
  • Not compatible with Fire TV (1st and 2nd Gen), Fire TV Stick (1st Gen), Element Fire TV Edition, Insignia HD/Insignia FHD, Hisense U6HF 4K ULED Fire TV Series, or Echo show 15.

“Alexa, find my remote.”

A remote that helps you find everything. Even itself.

Spend less time searching, more time watching. Just say, “Alexa, find my remote,” to any Amazon device with Alexa, Alexa built-in device, the Alexa app, or Fire TV app. A built-in speaker will emit a ring to lead you right to it. You can also use the Remote Finder button within the Fire TV mobile app. You can then use integrated TV controls or two customizable buttons to find and get to your entertainment quickly. App buttons may vary.

The Remote Finder feature has a range of up to 30ft (10m) and requires the Fire TV device to be on. Learn more here.

Lights up in the dark

Alexa Voice Remote Pro features backlit buttons that illuminate when you pick it up in a dimly-lit room. Now you can enjoy the action on-screen while keeping the home movie theater atmosphere going.

Your remote.
Your shortcuts.

Assign your favorite channels and apps to two customizable buttons for quick access to your content. You can also assign any of your favorite Alexa commands so you can turn on compatible smart lights, check the weather, or view your Ring camera with one touch. Just press and hold. Then select a shortcut option from the on-screen pop-up. You can easily choose recently-used apps, Alexa commands, or smart home controls to program. Learn more here.

Full sound. Zero disturbance.

A dedicated headphone button gives you quick access to your on-screen Bluetooth menu where you can easily pair or unpair your favorite audio device. So, whether you’re starting a late-night game session or relaxing with a movie, you can pair your wireless headphones with ease.

The all-in-one remote
with TV controls

Control your compatible TV, soundbar, and receiver with dedicated power, volume, and mute buttons. You can also surf live TV with dedicated channel buttons and get to your favorite shows and movies faster with preset app shortcuts (app buttons may vary). It’s expansive control and easy navigation without juggling multiple remotes.

From remote control to smart control

Go beyond your watchlist. Just press and ask, “Alexa, dim the lights,” to get movie night going or “Alexa, show me my front door,” to view a live feed from your Ring security camera. You can also use Alexa Voice Remote Pro to check the weather, play music, and control more of your favorite smart home functions right from the couch.

“Alexa, find action movies.“

Content shown may require subscription.

Compatible with most Fire TV devices

Alexa Voice Remote Pro requires a compatible Fire TV device. Not sure you have what you need? Check the compatibility guide.

How to set up

Step 1

Insert batteries to power up your Alexa Voice Remote Pro.

Step 2

Pair your remote with your Fire TV device. Learn more here.

Step 3

Follow the on-screen instructions to program the customizable buttons or learn more about the remote finder.

Every day is an earth day

You don’t have to be an environmental scientist to make sustainable choices. We considered sustainability in the design of this device. Here’s how:

Materials

17% post-consumer recycled plastic in the remote.

Device Packaging

This device’s packaging is 100% recyclable.

Fulfillment center packaging not included.

Product Certification (1)

Reducing CO2 products reduce their carbon footprint year after year. Certified by the Carbon Trust.

The Reducing CO2 label applies to products certified by the Carbon Trust, that are lowering their carbon emissions year after year for the full lifecycle of the product. The Carbon Trust was formed in 2001 and introduced the world’s first carbon label in 2007. It produces its certifications to global leading and independently verified standards. The Carbon Trust has a mission to accelerate the move to a sustainable, low carbon economy.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Amplify Your Entertainment: Alexa Voice Remote Pro
      Reviewed in the United States on June 1, 2023
      Configuration: Remote onlyVerified Purchase
      The Alexa Voice Remote Pro has proven to be an exceptional upgrade to my entertainment system, providing an enhanced level of control and convenience for my compatible Fire TV devices.

      One of the standout features of the Alexa Voice Remote Pro is the remote finder. How many times have we all lost the remote in the couch cushions or somewhere around the house? With this feature, those days are over. A simple command to Alexa - "Find my remote," and the remote emits a sound, making it easy to locate. This has saved me countless minutes of searching and a lot of frustration.

      The TV controls on this remote are comprehensive and intuitive. They allow me to control the power, volume, and mute functions of my TV, eliminating the need for multiple remotes and simplifying my entertainment setup. This consolidation of control into one device is a significant improvement in terms of convenience and efficiency.

      The backlit buttons are a feature that I didn't know I needed until I had them. They illuminate upon touch, making the remote easy to use in a dim or dark room. This thoughtful design feature enhances the user experience, especially during late-night movie marathons or early morning news sessions.

      The integration with Alexa is a game-changer, turning this remote into a powerful voice-activated tool. I can effortlessly launch apps, search for shows, play music, and even control smart home devices, all with simple voice commands. This hands-free control elevates the convenience of using my Fire TV devices to an entirely new level.

      This remote is designed to work with compatible Fire TV devices, and the pairing process is straightforward and quick. It operates smoothly and responsively, further enhancing the overall user experience.

      In terms of design, the remote is slim, lightweight, and comfortable to hold. The buttons have a satisfying tactile response, and the layout is intuitive, making it easy to navigate even without looking.

      In conclusion, the Alexa Voice Remote Pro is more than just a remote; it's a comprehensive control device for your entertainment and smart home needs. With its array of practical features, user-friendly design, and voice command capabilities, it greatly enhances the ease and enjoyment of using compatible Fire TV devices. If you're seeking to simplify and enrich your entertainment experience, the Alexa Voice Remote Pro is a must-have accessory.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Back-lit buttons did it for me!
      Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2022
      Configuration: Remote onlyVerified Purchase
      I recently purchased an Amazon Fire TV Stick 4K to eliminate an issue I had with my Vizio "Smart" 4K TV freezing up with apps, specifically Netflix. Problem solved (I'll review the Fire TV Stick 4K separately..it's great!).

      The remote that came with the Fire TV Stick 4k (on the left in the picture) worked great. Paired easily with my TV, Fire Stick and Alexa-enabled Echo Dot speaker. It really lacked only one thing that I wanted...back-lit buttons. I use this in my bedroom and at night in a dark room, fumbling to find the buttons was a pain. I could say "Alexa...rewind 30 seconds", etc and my Echo Dot would take over but I wanted to be able to make full use of the remote, separate from the Echo Dot so I'll concentrate my review on the remote itself.

      Here are the things that the "PRO" has that the "standard" Alexa Fire TV voice remote doesn't have:

      "Find My Remote": NOTE: If you already have an Alexa Voice remote, you will want to add the Pro as a second remote and keep your original to use this feature if you don't have an Echo Dot or other Voice enabled device. The "Find My Remote" feature is a definite plus. You just say "Alexa...find my remote" and the PRO will begin to beep until you find it and touch a button. It works with any Alexa device (including your old Alexa voice remote) and ALSO WORKS WITH THE ALEXA APP on your phone. The "beeping" isn't very loud, but it's loud enough to enable you to find the remote between sofa cushions.

      Back-lit buttons: My favorite feature, hands down. It lights up automatically when it senses movement or if you press any button. The other features are cool and useful, but I got spoiled having a universal remote with back-lit buttons.

      Bluetooth Headphone Pairing (top right button): Easily paired my Pioneer Bluetooth headphones with very good quality and no lag or delay in the audio. A nice feature, but I live alone so I don't use headphones for TV viewing, so it's nice to have, but didn't factor into my decision to buy it, but if it's something that you would use, it works great.

      In addition to the Volume Up/Down the Pro includes a Channel Up/Down button. I have no need for this very often but it's handy.

      Settings Button: The Pro has a button that takes you directly to the "Settings Menu" skipping the need to use the "Menu" button and having to navigate to Settings. I guess it's useful, but I don't see a need to access settings very often and using the blue Alexa Voice control button, you can just press it and say "Open Settings".

      2 Programmable Buttons on the PRO (labeled 1 and 2): Basically any command you give to Alexa, you can use these as a shortcut. You can also assign apps to them, etc. I assigned Button 1 to open HBOMAX and Button 2 to open YouTube TV as an example. The 4 quick-launch app buttons (Prime Video, Netflix, Disney+ and Hulu) at the bottom came as shown in my pic. In the product pics for this item above they are shown as blank buttons for some reason?

      I also have a Blink camera linked to my Alexa and can see a live shot from the camera on my TV with a quick voice command ("Show Camera Name") or I could assign that voice command to one of the 2 programmable buttons.

      When programming the buttons (a very easy process) it will show you your recent Alexa voice commands to choose from, you can choose "Apps" for a listing of all of your apps, etc. Same for games, etc.

      My decision to buy this rather than stick with the Alexa Voice remote that came with my Fire TV 4K was the Back-lit buttons.
      The headphone connection is cool, but I don't need it.
      The settings button I don't see my needing to access it often, so I don't care.
      Channel Up/Down button, only useful for me when using YouTube TV and I rarely channel surf so, I can live without it
      The 2 Programmable buttons: I like that I can have 2 extra apps to launch using one touch but I could just say "Launch HBOMAX" so maybe I'll find more fun or useful ways to use the buttons.

      ****When pressing the Blue Alexa Voice Button on the remote you don't need to say "Alexa" before giving the command. I did that once and had my Echo Dot trying to respond as well as the remote. lol

      In the end, I basically paid $35 so I could see the remote's buttons in the dark (I only paid $24.99 for the Fire TV Stick 4K with voice remote). LOL Was it worth it? I switched back to using the original one for one night and yes, not being able to see the buttons after being able to the night before is worth the $35 to eliminate the frustration. LOL

      I hope you find this review helpful.

      4.0 out of 5 stars Alexa Voice Remote Pro is Great for the Fire TV Cube! Controlling my TV/Cable box was not too good.
      Reviewed in the United States on May 31, 2023
      Configuration: Remote onlyVerified Purchase
      I purchased this Alexa Voice Remote Pro to compliment my Fire TV Cube. It is a little smaller than the original remote that comes with the Fire TV Cube. I like the Lighted Keypad and the buttons felt nice. I also like the ability to program the shortcut keys to open other apps, or a voice command. I had mine set up to open Plex. I wanted to be able to control my lights, but I discovered you can only "Turn On", or "Turn Off" with each button, so I would have to use both buttons to have complete control of my lights. There is not a "Toggle Power" option in Alexa's commands that I could find. Of course you can always push the blue button and just talk to Alexa to operate your lights, but I wanted to try the silent method.
      The reason for removing one star was I wanted to use this remote with my newly purchased Fire TV Cube to primarily control my Cable box and then also make use of Amazon's streaming services. For me this did not work out too well. I believe most of the issues I had came from the Fire TV Cube, but there were also limits here for me to watch cable easily. In my mind, I thought the TV with rabbit ears button would switch to my cable box. In fact, that button turns on the Channel Guide for the cable box, after the Fire TV Cube has been switched to cable. I was able to add a voice command to one of the shortcut buttons to switch to cable. For me, I think most of my Cable control issues originated in the Fire TV Cube, which I will also review. Otherwise, this is a great remote for using the streaming services available on Amazon.
